node.text:
.
When starting Bodies by Rachel I had one clear goal, to help educate and transform as many women's lives as possible. I wanted to show women how much fitness could change their lives, the way it did mine. Since then, BBR has grown into something so much bigger than I could have ever dreamed or imagined. Today, it's time to close one chapter, and say hello to a brand new future.

This is so much more than a name change. This is our first step in a new direction - a direction that I promise will provide you with more than you've ever imagined. 

✨New Coaches (announced soon)
✨New Challenges
✨Live Workouts (choose your coach and training style)
✨Browse Multiple Meal Guides (a nutrition experience like never before!)
✨Brand New Recipes 
✨Hundreds of New Workouts in our Workout Library 
✨Move your Mindset With @alexispredez
✨Favourite Recipes, Workouts & Videos

Updates to everything you know and love➕ we have a lot more on the way😻

None of this is possible without you, and every moment of love, sweat and tears that the Team and I have put into this has been done for you. This business has always been about one thing, our clients, and that will never, ever change. 

I have so much more to explain, and promise that I will answer ALL of your questions over the coming days so stay tuned on my Story for updates! 

LET'S MOVE❤️

node.title: Are you ready to...MOVE WITH US!🎉

.
Hiiiiii❤️

I’m currently eating 6x days in a mild deficit & 1x high day!

I decided to choose 4x meals from the @bodiesbyrachel App that I have not yet tried and well WOW🤤

The KEY to long term results are
✨Flexibility. 
Flexibility has allowed me to have so much control over what I eat. I failed at flexible dieting multiple times before I succeeded. It took me a long time to shift my mindset from ‘good’ and ‘bad’ food to just food/energy. 

This week we challenged our BBR girls to step outside their Meal Guides and use the BBR Food journal & Recipes to be flexible! It’s been amazing to watch so many of them over time transition into flexible dieting. 

✨Pre-Planning.
Being flexible still requires planning. I don’t think it matters how advanced you are. Planning is the key to success, but remember things don’t always go to plan, and we have to learn that it’s okay and we just do our beet to work around it. 

✨Consistency.
I don’t know how many times you’ve all heard me say this but consistency trumps perfection ANYDAY! Focus on all the small changes you are making because I promise you they add up. Mistakes are okay, they are great imo. Because we learn and we improve. We often learn more in our losses then we do in our success. 

✨ Education.
Keep learning, be eager to know more, experiment with new things. Having an understanding of why and how to do things correctly allows for more flexibility. 
-No protein shake, great I can have an egg white omelette instead.
-No laying hamstring curl machine, great I can use a dumbbell instead. 
The more we know, the easier this becomes.

Be patient, keep working, keep improving.
Whatever you do, don’t let your own journey overwhelm you, your inspos started somewhere too, remember that❤️

Let me know if you want to see a high day?

node.text:
.
.
One of my fave post workout meals!

So quick and easy, prepare yourself... these are delicious! 
.
Calories: 240.3
P: 20.7g  C: 28.8g  F: 4.7g⁣
⁣
✨ Ingredients:⁣
➡️ 1 wholemeal English Muffin⁣
➡️ 100g Egg Whites ⁣
➡️ 30g Turkey Breast Slices ⁣
➡️ 15g Vegan Mozzarella ⁣
➡️ Salt and Pepper, to taste ⁣⁣
⁣
✨ Optional Additions:⁣
➡️ Sugar Free BBQ or Tomato Sauce ⁣
⁣
✨ Method:⁣
1️⃣Spray a bowl with cooking spray. Pour egg whites into the bowl and place in a microwave for 90 seconds. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. 
⁣
2️⃣Lightly spray a pan on medium heat with coconut oil. When hot, add turkey slices and let them develop a slightly brown crust. Then add cheese and leave for an extra 30 seconds or until melted slightly. 
⁣
3️⃣Toast the english muffin while waiting. 
⁣
4️⃣Add the egg whites and turkey slices to the english muffin and top with a sauce of your choice! 
⁣
Enjoy!😍

WEEKEND PANCAKES ANYONE? This recipe is 🤤
.
Calories: 442.5⁣
P: 38.7g | C: 47.4g | F: 10.6g⁣
⁣
✨ Ingredients:⁣
➡️ 30g of Vanilla Protein Powder⁣
➡️ 25g of Blueberries⁣
➡️ Zest and Juice from 1/2 Lemon⁣
➡️ 8g of Honey⁣
➡️ 1 tsp of Vanilla Extract⁣
➡️ 60g of Rolled Oats⁣
➡️ 1 Egg(s)⁣
➡️ 1/4 tsp of Baking Soda⁣
➡️ 1 tbsp of Plant Based Milk⁣
⁣
✨ Optional Additions:⁣
➡️ Sugar Free Maple Syrup⁣
⁣
✨ Method:⁣
1️⃣ In a blender, combine protein, lemon juice, honey, vanilla extract, oats, egg, baking soda, and plant based milk. Blend until smooth. After blending, stir in blueberries and lemon zest.⁣
⁣
2️⃣ Lightly spray a pan on medium heat with coconut oil. When hot, pour enough pancake batter onto pan to create the desired size pancakes you'd like.⁣
⁣
3️⃣ When the pancake starts slightly bubbling at the surface, flip it to the other side and cook for another 1-2 minutes.⁣
⁣
4️⃣ Serve hot with sugar free maple syrup!⁣
⁣
💡Recipe hack: ⁣
➖ Prep and store your pancake batter in the freezer⁣
➖ Large silicone ice cube trays make for a great serving size⁣
➖ Let the batter defrost in silicone mold for 10-15 mins first⁣
➖ Cook on a low heat ⁣
⁣
Enjoy!😍

node.text:
“BE REAL”?

My question to you is, what exactly is real these days? 

To me, real is when someone is living their life authentically and exactly how they choose to. Expressing themselves through their style, music, art, work or whatever their passion may be, but owning it and embracing it wholeheartedly. 

I still remember years ago, shopping at City Beach for cute crops I couldn’t find in activewear shops and wearing them to the gym. I remember people commenting on what I would wear, and I completely understood it because I knew I chose to go against the ‘norm’. I was okay with other people not approving, because I approved and that is what mattered most. 

I spent so much of my time either working or training in the gym and had a burning passion for putting together cute outfits. Outfits I felt confident in, outfits I thought were cute and different! I chose to embrace a side of me that wasn’t necessarily accepted by others. 

If I had chosen to let others comments and opinions steer me away from being who I am and wearing what I like, I would never have started my own activewear line @cropshopboutique 

If there’s one thing I hope to teach young women it’s to embrace who you are. It’s to dare to be different, it’s to go after your dreams, silence the haters and make magic baby❤️

I don’t bring attention to negative comments because they upset me, but more because I know and see how many people deal with comments this in their day to day lives. I want you to know you are not alone, and I don’t want you to let people dim your light. 

Here to remind you to shine✨

node.text:
A little lock down series🤍

What’s everyone been doing to keep busy in lockdown?

I’m starting a #mwu1aday challenge! The goal is to do something small each day that makes me uncomfortable either physically, mentally or both! 

Join me each day on my stories❤️

node.text:
A DAY IN MY LIFE🤍 
My first ever fitness retreat!

So many beautiful memories made here.

A world with no coffee and no internet!
We spent our days;
✖️Waking up to sunlight instead of our phones.
✖️Walking in nature.
✖️Moving our bodies outside of the gym.
✖️Enjoying a variety of beautiful fresh food (a higher fat diet with less carbs which was something I had to get used to but didn’t mind the change).
✖️Incredible treatments & self care activities. 
✖️Connecting with beautiful people and having such meaningful conversations. 

Excited to be back journalling and attempting to meditate through breath work.

There is honestly so much happiness to be found within you❤️

MY TOP 3 QUICK & EASY ON THE GO BREAKFAST RECIPES😋

If you are anything like me, my mornings are always crazy so I love meals that are quick & easy to prepare!

That is exactly what you can expect from the @movewithus recipes! These 3 are taken straight from the app! They require minimal ingredients and are so easy to prepare on the go! 

Our meal guides cater to you and your personal goals! Honestly the most delicious recipes and we’ve been working hard to make flexible dieting so easy for you with our two brand new features launching! Meal swaps and Recipe Filters! Swap out a meal at the touch of a button and still stay on track to hit your overall targets for the day! 

1️⃣Basic Protein Oats
409 Calories
C50.9g F7.2g P28.8g
✖️70g Brown Sugar & Cinnamon Quick Oats
✖️30g Vanilla Protein Powder
✖️40g Raspberries 
✖️Cinnamon & Sugar Free Maple

2️⃣Emma’s Turkey & Avo Bagel
Calories 426
C54g F15g P20g
✖️1x Bagel
✖️4g Butter
✖️40g Avocado 
✖️60g Turkey Slices

3️⃣Egg White Breakfast Sandwich 
Calories 218
C24g F5g P19g
✖️1x English Muffin
✖️80g Egg Whites
✖️15g Turkey Slices 
✖️8g Cheese 

Enjoy❤️

node.text:
Body Update🙋🏽‍♀️

It has been such a long time since I’ve done a body update🙈 

Be kind I was so nervous posting this😬

Coming from a competing background where I would check in weekly, to now rarely doing it, I’ve decided to set myself a mini challenge for my birthday coming up! So here’s my first check in video for Bikini 4.0❤️

I always question if I should post videos of myself in a bikini. I don’t want it to come across the wrong way, but I’m also proud of the work I put in every day to build a strong body.

So I’m here to remind you, like I often remind myself, you don’t have to put yourself in one single box. 

I can feel confident in a bikini and I can also have days where I don’t. 

I can enjoy tracking my calories but I can also enjoy intuitive eating.

I can love to lift weights and I can also love cardio/pilates/yoga. 

I can love being productive and I can also love being lazy. 

I can love wearing cute outfits and makeup to the gym and also love wearing no makeup and baggy clothes to the gym. 

I can love whole nutritious foods, but also love fast food and sweets. 

I can love going out and also love staying in.

You don’t have to be one or the other. Society doesn’t choose who you are, you do. 

Allow yourself to be you, in whatever form that may be. Allow yourself to go through it, just know you’ll always come out the other side❤️

MY TRAINING SPLIT🔥

BIKINI 4.0, WHOS IN🥵

As always I trial any challenge before it goes live, so Bikini 4.0 it’s been for me! Very challenging, but very worth it!

I have been in a mild surplus and feel like I’m in a great place to now come back down to maintenance😍

🍑Monday: Glutes Weighted
💪🏼Tuesday: Shoulders, Back & Core
🥵Wednesday: Full Body Circuit
(LISS Cardio Optional)
🍑Thursday: Glutes Weighted
🙆🏽‍♀️Friday: Mobility & Rest Day
(Core Optional)
🔥Saturday: Quads & Hamstrings 
🤍Sunday: Rest Day

I am going to do a full break down of the split on my story🤍

THIS NEW CSB BARE SET👀🥲

FULL BODY CIRCUIT🔥

As promised a minimal equipment workout! All you need is a bench!

Honestly DO NOT underestimate body weight workouts! I was feeling every bit of this🥵

1️⃣20x Sumo Squat Heel Pulse Combo
2️⃣20x Wide Frog Squats
3️⃣10x Box Jumps 
3 Sets

1️⃣10x Walk Outs/Push Up
2️⃣20x Shoulder Taps 
3️⃣20x Plank Raises 
3 Sets 

1️⃣10x Step Ups E/L
2️⃣20x Up and Overs
2 Sets 

1️⃣10x Incline Push Ups
2️⃣20x Tricep Dips
2 Sets 

Enjoy🙊❤️

node.text:
Moments from the weekend❤️

Balancing Happiness✨

Happiness is different for everyone. I spent a good 4 years of my life working 24/7. I took so much joy from helping other women unlock their potential. I loved the feeling of working hard and seeing the progress. However I also lost any balance outside of my work. I used to tell my self ‘work life balance doesn’t exist’, but that was just an excuse for neglecting looking after me and nourishing the amazing relationships I had around me. 

I used to feel guilty for enjoying myself outside of my work. But I quickly learnt you can’t be your best if you are burnt out and over worked and it’s so important to balance your happiness. 

I absolutely love what I do everyday. I work so incredibly hard but you cannot let your work become your only identity. You have so much to offer the world and the people around you. 

So yes, I love the hustle and I love the person I’ve become pushing myself to the lengths I have. I understand that we have fitness and business goals but it’s so important that you also look after you. You need to make amazing memories, you need to laugh, you need to be playful, you need to be happy outside of your work❤️

Life is short so wear that dress, go to that event, tell the people close to you, you love them and never regret doing what makes you happy. 

Don’t let your fitness and career goals stop you from balancing your happiness❤️
